1
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:35,561
<i>[CARSON] I ALWAYS THOUGHT</i>
<i>DEATH WOULD BE DIFFERENT.</i>

2
00:01:35,563 --> 00:01:39,231
<i>I EXPECTED A</i>
<i>GREAT WAVE OF REALIZATION</i>
<i>TO SWEEP OVER ME.</i>

3
00:01:39,233 --> 00:01:41,567
<i>SUDDENLY, THE MEANING OF LIFE</i>
<i>WOULD BE ANSWERED ALONG WITH</i>

4
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:43,735
<i>EVERY OTHER QUESTION</i>
<i>I EVER HAD.</i>

5
00:01:43,737 --> 00:01:45,537
<i>BUT THERE WAS</i>
<i>NOTHING TO REALIZE.</i>

6
00:01:45,539 --> 00:01:47,206
<i>- I WAS DEAD.</i>
<i>- [DOORBELL RINGS]</i>

7
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:49,875
- WHAT?!
- ARE YOU SHERYL PHILLIPS?

8
00:01:49,877 --> 00:01:52,478
WHAT, DID I FORGET TO PUT MY
TRASH BINS AWAY OR SOMETHING?

9
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,513
NO, MA'AM.
YOUR SON HAS DIED.

10
00:01:54,515 --> 00:01:57,349
HIS BODY WAS FOUND
IN THE SCHOOL PARKING LOT
THIS MORNING.

11
00:01:57,351 --> 00:01:59,718
<i>[STUDENT REPORTER]</i>
<i>A FEW DAYS AGO,</i>

12
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:02,254
RIGHT HERE WHERE I'M STANDING,
CLOVER HIGH SCHOOL SENIOR

13
00:02:02,256 --> 00:02:05,257
CARSON PHILLIPS
LOST HIS LIFE WHEN HE WAS
STRUCK BY LIGHTNING.

14
00:02:05,259 --> 00:02:08,327
A SERVICE
WILL BE HELD THIS SUNDAY
AT CLOVER COMMUNITY CHAPEL.

15
00:02:08,329 --> 00:02:11,263
HE WILL BE MISSED.

16
00:02:11,265 --> 00:02:14,266
♪ IT'S SO HARD

17
00:02:14,268 --> 00:02:18,137
♪ TO SAY GOODBYE

18
00:02:18,139 --> 00:02:25,277
♪ TO YESTERDAY

19
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:27,279
<i>AND...MY FUNERAL SUCKS.</i>

20
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:28,780
GOODBYE, CARSON.

21
00:02:28,782 --> 00:02:30,616
<i>YOU'VE SEEN MY END.</i>

22
00:02:30,618 --> 00:02:32,918
<i>BUT WHERE DO I BEGIN?</i>

23
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:36,522
<i>I REMEMBER WHEN</i>
<i>I REALIZED I WAS DIFFERENT</i>
<i>FROM EVERYONE ELSE.</i>

24
00:02:36,524 --> 00:02:39,391
MY NAME IS CARSON.
MY MOM SAYS I WAS NAMED CARSON

25
00:02:39,393 --> 00:02:42,361
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT WAS ON TV
WHEN I WAS CONCEIVED.

26
00:02:42,363 --> 00:02:45,297
WHEN SOMETHING
TAKES AWAY SOMETHING ELSE,
WHAT DO WE CALL THAT?

27
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:47,933
- NOT ADDITION, BUT...
- HOMICIDE.

28
00:02:47,935 --> 00:02:50,269
<i>I WAS ADVANCED AT A YOUNG AGE.</i>

29
00:02:50,271 --> 00:02:51,803
MOST OF THE FOUNDING FATHERS

30
00:02:51,805 --> 00:02:54,173
WERE CLOSETED HOMOSEXUALS
AND SLAVE OWNERS.

31
00:02:54,175 --> 00:02:56,909
<i>MY REPORTS WERE ALWAYS</i>
<i>MORE THOROUGH THAN MY PEERS.</i>

32
00:02:56,911 --> 00:02:58,877
I'M SERIOUS.

33
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:01,480
<i>I REMEMBER WHEN I DISCOVERED</i>
<i>THE POWER OF WORDS</i>

34
00:03:01,482 --> 00:03:03,916
<i>AND HOW EASY IT WAS</i>
<i>TO ESCAPE INTO A WORLD</i>
<i>OF MY OWN BY USING THEM.</i>

35
00:03:03,918 --> 00:03:06,485
[NEAL]
IT WAS A PLEASANT ENVIRONMENT.
THREE SHEETS TO THE WIND, TOO.

36
00:03:06,487 --> 00:03:09,821
YOU'RE ALREADY.
AT LEAST LEAVE ME ONE BEER.

37
00:03:09,823 --> 00:03:12,491
CARSON, THIS IS
THE LAST TIME YOU'LL EVER
SEE YOUR GRANDFATHER!

38
00:03:12,493 --> 00:03:15,494
- I KNOW WHAT HE LOOKS LIKE!
- STOP FIGHTING ME!

39
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:20,666
STAND UP.

40
00:03:20,668 --> 00:03:22,634
- BOO!
- AHH!

41
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:24,770
WHAT THE HELL
IS WRONG WITH YOU?!

42
00:03:24,772 --> 00:03:27,372
IT WAS LAME.
I KNOW, I KNOW.

43
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:29,341
THE KID'S A PUSS.

44
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:31,210
<i>I REMEMBER THE DAY</i>
<i>GRANDMA CAME TO LIVE WITH US.</i>

45
00:03:31,212 --> 00:03:33,679
GRANDMA!

46
00:03:33,681 --> 00:03:35,614
<i>[NEAL]</i>
<i>IT'S THE FIFTH TIME</i>
<i>YOU FOUND HER</i>

47
00:03:35,616 --> 00:03:36,682
<i>WONDERING AROUND TOWN.</i>

48
00:03:36,684 --> 00:03:38,517
OH, MOM.

49
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:40,419
AND NOW
SHE'S IN THE LINEN CLOSET.

50
00:03:40,421 --> 00:03:42,521
YOUR BEDROOM IS THE NEXT DOOR.

51
00:03:42,523 --> 00:03:44,590
<i>AND THE DAY</i>
<i>THAT GRANDMA GOT SICK.</i>

52
00:03:44,592 --> 00:03:47,693
- I WROTE YOU A STORY, GRANDMA.
- OH, LET'S SEE.

53
00:03:47,695 --> 00:03:52,364
"ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A BOY."

54
00:03:52,366 --> 00:03:54,366
WELL, IT COULD USE
A LITTLE DEVELOPMENT,

55
00:03:54,368 --> 00:03:56,235
BUT IT'S A GREAT BEGINNING.

56
00:03:56,237 --> 00:03:57,903
<i>THE WHOLE NEIGHBORHOOD</i>
<i>REMEMBERS THE NIGHT</i>

57
00:03:57,905 --> 00:04:00,239
<i>THAT DAD LEFT.</i>

58
00:04:00,241 --> 00:04:03,375
WE JUST STARTED
GOING BACK TO COUNSELING.
YOU CAN'T JUST DO THIS.

59
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:05,244
YEAH, WELL, I'M LEAVING.
I CAN'T TAKE THIS.

60
00:04:05,246 --> 00:04:07,713
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?!
- ANYWHERE BUT HERE.

61
00:04:07,715 --> 00:04:10,549
- THAT'S MINE!
- THAT IS NOT YOURS.

62
00:04:10,551 --> 00:04:12,551
I...THANK YOU.

63
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:14,386
YOU CAN'T COME BACK!

64
00:04:14,388 --> 00:04:15,454
NO!

65
00:04:15,456 --> 00:04:16,855
I HATE YOU!

66
00:04:16,857 --> 00:04:19,691
<i>[SOBBING]</i>
<i>I HATE YOU!</i>

67
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:21,560
SCREW IT.

68
00:04:21,562 --> 00:04:24,396
IF ANYONE ASKS,
WE'RE JEWISH.

69
00:04:24,398 --> 00:04:29,901
<i>IT'S BEEN ME AND MOM</i>
<i>EVER SINCE.</i>

70
00:04:29,903 --> 00:04:32,271
MOM, WAKE UP.

71
00:04:32,273 --> 00:04:33,905
YOU PASSED OUT AGAIN.

72
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:36,541
- WAKE UP, MOM.
- OH, JESUS!

73
00:04:36,543 --> 00:04:38,777
CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU SURVIVED THE NIGHT.

74
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:42,748
OH, JESUS.
IF YOU WERE DESCENT,
YOU WOULD JUST LET ME SLEEP.

75
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:45,584
IF I WAS DESCENT,
I'D JUST PUT YOU TO SLEEP.

76
00:04:45,586 --> 00:04:48,620
MY GOD.
MY HEAD.

77
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:50,722
YOU KNOW, THE MORNING
ISN'T SUPPOSED TO HURT.

78
00:04:50,724 --> 00:04:52,591
I DON'T HAVE TO GO TO SCHOOL.

79
00:04:52,593 --> 00:04:57,429
WHY DO I HAVE TO GET UP?

80
00:04:57,431 --> 00:04:58,997
HERE.

81
00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:00,799
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE DRINKING

82
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,901
WITH ALL THOSE PILLS
DR. DIEHLER'S GIVING YOU?

83
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:05,937
DR. WHEELER. WHY DON'T YOU JUST
LEAVE THAT TO THE PROFESSIONALS?

84
00:05:05,939 --> 00:05:07,839
CAN I HAVE MY OTHER GLASS
BACK, PLEASE?

85
00:05:07,841 --> 00:05:09,941
IT'S IN THE SINK.
GET IT YOURSELF.

86
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:12,678
YOU KNOW, YOU MAKE ME WISH I'D
HAD THAT ABORTION IN THE '90s.

87
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,080
- THAT MAKES TWO OF US.
- GO TO SCHOOL ALREADY!

88
00:05:15,082 --> 00:05:16,882
GO! GO! GO!

89
00:05:16,884 --> 00:05:19,051
AND IF I AM STILL SLEEPING
WHEN YOU GET HOME,

90
00:05:19,053 --> 00:05:24,456
DON'T YOU DARE PUT MY HAND
IN A BOWL OF WATER AGAIN.

91
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,525
- [LAUGHS]
- SHUT UP.

92
00:05:26,527 --> 00:05:27,959
BYE. LOVE YOU, TOO.

93
00:05:27,961 --> 00:05:30,629
WOULD YOU BRING ME
MY PILLOW BACK?!

94
00:05:30,631 --> 00:05:32,798
CLOSE THE SHADES.

95
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,334
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- I HATE YOU.

96
00:05:35,336 --> 00:05:37,336
<i>HIGH SCHOOL.</i>

97
00:05:37,338 --> 00:05:39,604
<i>SOCIETY'S BRIGHT IDEA</i>
<i>TO PUT ALL THEIR AGGRESSIVE,</i>

98
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:42,341
<i>SELF RIGHTEOUS,</i>
<i>PUBESCENT, NAIVE YOUTH</i>
<i>INTO ONE ENVIRONMENT</i>

99
00:05:42,343 --> 00:05:44,943
<i>TO TORMENT</i>
<i>AND EMOTIONALLY SCAR</i>
<i>EACH OTHER FOR LIFE.</i>

100
00:05:44,945 --> 00:05:50,982
CATTLE, CATTLE,
CATTLE, CATTLE!

101
00:05:50,984 --> 00:05:55,354
<i>SHAKESPEARE ONCE WROTE</i>
<i>THAT LIFE IS BUT A DREAM.</i>

102
00:05:55,356 --> 00:05:57,823
<i>AND THAT'S EXACTLY</i>
<i>HOW I LIVED MY LIFE,</i>

103
00:05:57,825 --> 00:06:00,025
<i>FROM ONE DREAM TO THE NEXT.</i>

104
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:02,928
<i>HATING EVERY</i>
<i>UPDATE OF REALITY.</i>

105
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:06,098
WELL, THE "I" STANDS FOR
AN IMAGINARY NUMBER.

106
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,700
OKAY, HOLD UP.
THERE ARE IMAGINARY
NUMBERS NOW?

107
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:11,570
ARE THERE
UNICORNS THE NEXT LESSON?
CAN SOMEONE PLEASE

108
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:14,906
TEACH ME SOMETHING USEFUL,
LIKE HOW TO BALANCE A CHECKBOOK?

109
00:06:14,908 --> 00:06:17,509
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
WHY DID I GET A "C" ON THIS?

110
00:06:17,511 --> 00:06:19,845
- THIS IS A GREAT PAPER.
- THE ASSIGNMENT WAS TO PICK

111
00:06:19,847 --> 00:06:22,514
EITHER EVOLUTION OR CREATIONISM
AND PROVIDE BACKGROUND EVIDENCE

112
00:06:22,516 --> 00:06:24,516
AS TO WHY
YOU BELIEVE THAT THEORY.

113
00:06:24,518 --> 00:06:26,852
I KNOW.
I PICKED EVOLUTION.

114
00:06:26,854 --> 00:06:29,788
I SAID THAT IT'S
OBVIOUS CREATURES CAN ADAPT
TO THEIR ENVIRONMENTS

115
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,391
BECAUSE I NO LONGER
HAVE THE URGE TO THROW THINGS

116
00:06:32,393 --> 00:06:34,860
AT STUDENTS
WHO BELIEVE IN CREATIONISM.

117
00:06:34,862 --> 00:06:36,695
RIGHT?

118
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:37,996
RIGHT?

119
00:06:37,998 --> 00:06:40,866
I BELIEVE IN CREATIONISM.

120
00:06:40,868 --> 00:06:42,768
EXHIBIT "A."

121
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:44,736
WELCOME TO CAREER DAY
HERE AT THE COUNSELING CENTER.

122
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,905
RIGHT, I'M SURE
YOU SAW OUR FLIER.

123
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:49,408
AND YOU KNOW,
WE'RE HERE TO JUST SORT OF
HELP YOU KIDDOS

124
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:52,978
ESTABLISH YOUR
FUTURE CAREER OPTIONS,
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO...

125
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:55,013
I KNOW THE EXACT CAREER
THAT I WANT.

126
00:06:55,015 --> 00:06:56,782
OKAY.
WHAT IS IT, MUNCHKIN?

127
00:06:56,784 --> 00:06:58,750
I WANT TO BE THE EDITOR
OF <i>THE NEW YORKER</i>

128
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:01,520
AND THE YOUNGEST
FREELANCE JOURNALIST
TO BE PUBLISHED

129
00:07:01,522 --> 00:07:03,188
IN <i>THE NEW YORK TIMES,</i>
<i>LA TIMES, BOSTON HERALD,</i>
<i>AND</i> <i>THE CHICAGO TRIBUNE.</i>

130
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:05,724
YOU HAVE HAD SOME TIME
TO THINK ABOUT THIS THEN, HUH?

131
00:07:05,726 --> 00:07:09,428
- EVERY DAY SINCE I WAS EIGHT.
- OKAY. WELL...

132
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:13,165
WHAT ABOUT COLLEGE?
I CAN HELP YOU DECIDE
WHAT COLLEGE TO GO TO.

133
00:07:13,167 --> 00:07:15,534
UH, NO. I'VE GOT
TO GET INTO NORTHWESTERN.

134
00:07:15,536 --> 00:07:17,836
ALL RIGHT.
WHERE IS THAT EXACTLY?

135
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:20,672
- ILLINOIS.
- NEVER HEARD OF IT.

136
00:07:20,674 --> 00:07:24,509
I'VE PUT 17 GOOD YEARS
INTO THIS TOWN, OKAY?

137
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:26,778
PEOPLE SPEND LESS TIME
IN PRISON FOR MURDER SENTENCES.

138
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,914
- IS THAT TRUE?
- YES. YES, LOOK IT UP.

139
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:31,082
I'VE BEEN THE PRESIDENT
OF THE WRITERS' CLUB

140
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:33,452
AND THE EDITOR OF THE NEWSPAPER
SINCE SOPHOMORE YEAR

141
00:07:33,454 --> 00:07:35,787
JUST TO BETTER MY CHANCES
OF GETTING INTO THAT SCHOOL.

142
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:37,923
THAT IS SO SMART.

143
00:07:37,925 --> 00:07:40,926
- WOW.
- IT'S BEEN CHALLENGING.

144
00:07:40,928 --> 00:07:44,663
SO I'VE ALREADY APPLIED
AND I MEET ALL THE REQUIREMENTS.

145
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:47,532
I JUST HAVEN'T
HEARD BACK FROM THEM.

146
00:07:47,534 --> 00:07:49,634
SO I'D APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU UM,

147
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,937
MAYBE FOUND OUT WHY.

148
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:55,607
OKAY. AND THAT IS
SOMETHING THAT I WOULD DO?
I WOULD CALL THEM?

149
00:07:55,609 --> 00:07:57,209
- YES.
- OKAY.

150
00:07:57,211 --> 00:07:59,778
I WILL DO ANYTHING
TO GET INTO THAT SCHOOL.

151
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:01,947
- I MEAN ANYTHING.
- I'M ON IT.

152
00:08:01,949 --> 00:08:04,783
BUT SINCE YOU'RE HERE,
HOW 'BOUT YOU JUST FILL OUT THIS

153
00:08:04,785 --> 00:08:07,118
CLOVER COMMUNITY COLLEGE
APPLICATION.

154
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,887
'CAUSE WITH EVERY APPLICATION,

155
00:08:08,889 --> 00:08:10,956
I GET A POINT
TOWARDS A JUICE CUP.

156
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,791
AHEM. DO YOU JUICE?

157
00:08:12,793 --> 00:08:14,960
BECAUSE IT'S REALLY
CHANGED HOW I FEEL.

158
00:08:14,962 --> 00:08:17,629
LAST WEEK'S EDITION OF
THE <i>CLOVER HIGH CHRONICLE</i>

159
00:08:17,631 --> 00:08:20,098
WAS YET
ANOTHER DISAPPOINTMENT.

160
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:23,134
WE DID HAVE NEW MATERIAL
FOR EACH OF THE SECTIONS,

161
00:08:23,136 --> 00:08:25,637
BUT ONCE AGAIN,

162
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:28,507
IT WAS ALL WRITTEN BY ME.

163
00:08:28,509 --> 00:08:31,576
NOW THIS,
THIS HAS TO STOP.

164
00:08:31,578 --> 00:08:34,045
THIS IS NOT THE
<i>CARSON PHILLIPS CHRONICLE.</i>

165
00:08:34,047 --> 00:08:36,515
ALL RIGHT? IT'S THE
<i>CLOVER HIGH CHRONICLE.</i>

166
00:08:36,517 --> 00:08:38,850
CARSON PHILLIPS.
CLOVER HIGH.

167
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,853
HOPEFULLY,
THIS WEEK WILL BE DIFFERENT.

168
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:46,091
DWAYNE! DO YOU HAVE
THAT MOVIE REVIEW READY
FOR    <i>MANSLAUGHTER 3 YET?</i>

169
00:08:46,093 --> 00:08:47,559
- YES.
- YEAH?

170
00:08:47,561 --> 00:08:49,094
- NO.
- NO.

171
00:08:49,096 --> 00:08:50,829
I WENT,
BUT I PASSED OUT.

172
00:08:50,831 --> 00:08:52,264
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
IT WAS GONNA BE IN 3D.

173
00:08:52,266 --> 00:08:54,766
- IT WASN'T.
- WHOA.

174
00:08:54,768 --> 00:08:58,003
VICKI. DO YOU HAVE
YOUR WEATHER REPORT READY?

175
00:08:58,005 --> 00:09:05,176
- WHAT?
- YOUR WEATHER REPORT.

176
00:09:05,178 --> 00:09:08,547
YEAH, IT'S CLOUDY.

177
00:09:08,549 --> 00:09:10,682
OKAY. THANK YOU, VICKI.

178
00:09:10,684 --> 00:09:12,117
PROGRESS, RIGHT?

179
00:09:12,119 --> 00:09:15,153
AND UH, EMILIO,

180
00:09:15,155 --> 00:09:18,757
DO YOU HAVE A SECTION
YOU'D LIKE TO TACKLE THIS WEEK?

181
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:22,794
UH...I LOVE AMERICA.

182
00:09:22,796 --> 00:09:25,297
OKAY. GREAT.

183
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:27,566
I LOVE THE APHORISM.

184
00:09:27,568 --> 00:09:29,834
WE'LL CREATE
A PATRIOTIC SECTION
JUST FOR YOU.

185
00:09:29,836 --> 00:09:31,703
NOW.

186
00:09:31,705 --> 00:09:34,639
MOVING ONTO CREATIVE WRITING.
DOES ANYONE HAVE ANY

187
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:36,608
- SHORT STORIES OR--
- YES, I DID WRITE

188
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:38,243
- A SHORT STORY.
- FANTASTIC. LET'S HEAR IT.

189
00:09:38,245 --> 00:09:44,716
UM...

190
00:09:44,718 --> 00:09:50,221
THIS IS WRITTEN BY MALERIE.

191
00:09:50,223 --> 00:09:52,223
"IT WAS THE BEST OF TIMES.

192
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:54,192
"IT WAS THE WORST OF TIMES.

193
00:09:54,194 --> 00:09:56,127
IT WAS THE AGE OF WISDOM."

194
00:09:56,129 --> 00:09:59,164
MALERIE.
YOU DIDN'T WRITE THAT.

195
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:01,333
YEAH,
IT'S IN MY HANDWRITING.

196
00:10:01,335 --> 00:10:04,135
BUT UM...

197
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:07,806
IF YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME THEN...

198
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:10,075
- [PERIOD BELL RINGS]
- PLEASE COME BACK TOMORROW

199
00:10:10,077 --> 00:10:12,744
WITH SOMETHING, WITH ANYTHING.
AND DON'T FORGET THAT THERE'S

200
00:10:12,746 --> 00:10:14,913
A WRITERS' CLUB MEETING
IN CASE ANY OF YOU

201
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,248
CHANGE YOUR MIND
ABOUT WANTING TO JOIN.

202
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:22,754
OR CHANGE YOUR PERSONALITIES.

203
00:10:22,756 --> 00:10:25,256
<i>THERE WAS NEVER ANYTHING</i>
<i>TO DO IN CLOVER...</i>

204
00:10:25,258 --> 00:10:27,258
<i>BESIDES JAMBA JUICE</i>
<i>AND COW TIPPING.</i>

205
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,094
THERE'S NO "H" IN SUCK!

206
00:10:29,096 --> 00:10:31,329
<i>SO TO ENTERTAIN OURSELVES,</i>
<i>WE ALL BECAME</i>

