00:53:42,520 --> 00:53:44,587
GET OUT.
I DO NOT KNOW YOU!

1080
00:53:44,589 --> 00:53:46,889
ALL RIGHT,
OKAY, I'M LEAVING.

1081
00:53:46,891 --> 00:53:49,825
<i>[CLAIRE]</i>
<i>SO WE STILL NEED A VENUE</i>
<i>FOR PROM, ANY IDEAS?</i>

1082
00:53:49,827 --> 00:53:51,427
I WAS THINKING
QUAIL GARDENS.

1083
00:53:51,429 --> 00:53:53,395
WHAT ABOUT
MOTEL 6 UP THE HIGHWAY?

1084
00:53:53,397 --> 00:53:56,498
I MEAN, EVERYONE HEADS UP THERE
AFTER PROM ANYWAY, RIGHT?

1085
00:53:56,500 --> 00:53:58,867
ANY OBJECTIONS
TO QUAIL GARDENS?

1086
00:53:58,869 --> 00:54:00,636
[TOGETHER]
NO OBJECTIONS.

1087
00:54:00,638 --> 00:54:02,404
ISN'T QUAIL GARDENS

1088
00:54:02,406 --> 00:54:04,540
LIKE RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE COUNTRY?

1089
00:54:04,542 --> 00:54:06,875
AND PROM IS USUALLY
IN THE BEGINNING OF SUMMER

1090
00:54:06,877 --> 00:54:09,445
SO EVERYONE'S GONNA BE
EATEN ALIVE BY BUGS.

1091
00:54:09,447 --> 00:54:12,348
I THINK THE UH,
THE CLOVER DINING HALL
WOULD BE CHEAPER

1092
00:54:12,350 --> 00:54:14,383
- AND SMARTER.
- OKAY,

1093
00:54:14,385 --> 00:54:15,918
CLOVER DINING HALL IT IS.

1094
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:18,854
- AWESOME, MOVING ON.
- WE NEED A THEME.

1095
00:54:18,856 --> 00:54:21,390
HOW 'BOUT
A FAIRY TALE THEME?
WE COULD DO

1096
00:54:21,392 --> 00:54:23,559
AN EASY
CINDERELLA SETTING
FOR PHOTOS.

1097
00:54:23,561 --> 00:54:26,262
OH, MY GOD.
I LOVE RAPUNZEL.

1098
00:54:26,264 --> 00:54:28,731
YEAH, I'M NOT SURE
ALL THE STUDENTS

1099
00:54:28,733 --> 00:54:31,600
WOULD APPRECIATE
UM, THAT THEME.

1100
00:54:31,602 --> 00:54:33,435
LIKE THE MALE ONES.

1101
00:54:33,437 --> 00:54:35,604
WHY DON'T YOU GUYS DO
LIKE A, UH, ERA THEME,

1102
00:54:35,606 --> 00:54:38,607
LIKE THE ROARING '20s
OR SOMETHING?

1103
00:54:38,609 --> 00:54:40,576
[SIGHS]
'20s IS FINE.

1104
00:54:40,578 --> 00:54:42,611
SUPER.

1105
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:45,281
OKAY.
WHY ARE YOU GUYS, UH,

1106
00:54:45,283 --> 00:54:47,683
LETTING ME MAKE
ALL THE DECISIONS?

1107
00:54:47,685 --> 00:54:50,019
IT WAS A LOT MORE FUN
WHEN I GOT TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

1108
00:54:50,021 --> 00:54:59,628
ARE YOU GONNA MAKE US
WRITE MORE IF WE DO?

1109
00:54:59,630 --> 00:55:01,597
- ANYTHING FOR ME?
- NO,

1110
00:55:01,599 --> 00:55:03,766
JUST BILLS AND ADS

1111
00:55:03,768 --> 00:55:05,934
AND BILLS, BILLS, BILLS.

1112
00:55:05,936 --> 00:55:07,936
LET ME SEE.

1113
00:55:07,938 --> 00:55:09,772
MAGAZINES...

1114
00:55:09,774 --> 00:55:12,374
UH, LET ME KNOW
IF YOU FIND ANYTHING.

1115
00:55:12,376 --> 00:55:22,318
- YEP.
- THANK YOU.

1116
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:23,719
HOWDY.

1117
00:55:23,721 --> 00:55:25,688
HERE IS MY ENTRY
FOR THE MAGAZINE.

1118
00:55:25,690 --> 00:55:28,624
UH, GREAT.
IS IT ABOUT CONTRACEPTION?

1119
00:55:28,626 --> 00:55:31,060
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT MUST BE REALLY NICE

1120
00:55:31,062 --> 00:55:33,796
TO HAVE PLANS
TO JOURNEY OUT INTO THE WORLD,

1121
00:55:33,798 --> 00:55:36,031
BUT SOME OF US
DON'T HAVE THAT CAPABILITY.

1122
00:55:36,033 --> 00:55:38,867
SOME OF US ARE STUCK HERE
AND HAVE TO MAKE THE MOST OF IT,

1123
00:55:38,869 --> 00:55:41,970
SO EXCUSE ME FOR WANTING TO HAVE
A LITTLE FUN MY SENIOR YEAR.

1124
00:55:41,972 --> 00:55:45,341
IT COULD BE
THE LAST CHANCE THAT I GET.

1125
00:55:45,343 --> 00:55:47,976
AND WHY ARE YOU INCAPABLE?

1126
00:55:47,978 --> 00:55:54,350
WHY ARE YOU STUCK HERE?

1127
00:55:54,352 --> 00:55:56,819
SECOND GRADE
MRS. McCOY'S CLASSROOM.

1128
00:55:56,821 --> 00:55:59,088
I DOUBT
YOU REMEMBER THIS,
BUT I DO.

1129
00:55:59,090 --> 00:56:02,057
WE WENT AROUND THE ROOM AND
WE ALL SAID WHAT WE WANTED TO BE

1130
00:56:02,059 --> 00:56:04,993
WHEN WE GREW UP.
I SAID THAT I WANTED TO BE
A NOBEL PEACE PRIZE WINNER

1131
00:56:04,995 --> 00:56:07,896
- AND YOU SAID...
- I WANTED TO BE A BALLERINA.

1132
00:56:07,898 --> 00:56:10,366
WHAT STOPPED YOU?

1133
00:56:10,368 --> 00:56:15,671
- THEY ALL LAUGHED AT ME.
- BUT I DIDN'T LAUGH AT YOU.

1134
00:56:15,673 --> 00:56:18,674
IN WHAT GRADE DO WE
STOP BELIEVING IN OURSELVES?

1135
00:56:18,676 --> 00:56:21,844
WELL, WHAT GRADE DO WE
JUST STOP BELIEVING PERIOD?

1136
00:56:21,846 --> 00:56:24,613
I MEAN, SOMEONE HAS TO BE
A NOBEL PEACE PRIZE WINNER.

1137
00:56:24,615 --> 00:56:26,849
SOMEONE
HAS TO BE A BALLERINA.

1138
00:56:26,851 --> 00:56:32,020
WHY NOT US?

1139
00:56:32,022 --> 00:56:33,789
[SIGHS]

1140
00:56:33,791 --> 00:56:36,091
NOW I CAN'T BE
THE ONLY ONE THAT GETS THAT.

1141
00:56:36,093 --> 00:56:39,161
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1142
00:56:39,163 --> 00:56:41,530
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I'M HERE AT SCHOOL,

1143
00:56:41,532 --> 00:56:43,465
I JUST TURN MY PHONE OFF

1144
00:56:43,467 --> 00:56:45,768
SO THAT I DON'T HEAR IT
NOT RINGING.

1145
00:56:45,770 --> 00:56:48,704
- [RINGING CONTINUES]
- WHO IS IT?

1146
00:56:48,706 --> 00:56:54,543
IT'S...MY DAD.

1147
00:56:54,545 --> 00:56:55,711
HELLO?

1148
00:56:55,713 --> 00:56:57,946
HEY, CARSON.

1149
00:56:57,948 --> 00:57:00,015
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO CALL YOU AFTER SCHOOL.
I'M SURE YOU'RE BUSY

1150
00:57:00,017 --> 00:57:02,618
WITH YOUR HOMEWORK AND SO FORTH
BUT I GOT SOME REALLY GOOD NEWS

1151
00:57:02,620 --> 00:57:07,022
I WANNA TELL YOU.
YEAH, I'M GETTING MARRIED.
HER NAME'S APRIL.

1152
00:57:07,024 --> 00:57:10,025
WE'RE EXPECTING
A BABY AND YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE A BABY BROTHER.

1153
00:57:10,027 --> 00:57:11,994
YOU GOTTA BE SHITTING ME.

1154
00:57:11,996 --> 00:57:14,730
SO ANYWAY,
SHE WANTS TO MEET YOU.
IS THERE ANY CHANCE

1155
00:57:14,732 --> 00:57:16,899
YOU COULD MAKE IT
OVER FOR DINNER SOMETIME SOON?

1156
00:57:16,901 --> 00:57:19,902
I...I'D HAVE
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

1157
00:57:19,904 --> 00:57:21,904
PLEASE DO.
IN FACT,

1158
00:57:21,906 --> 00:57:25,073
I'D REALLY APPRECIATE IT.
HOPE TO SEE YOU SOON. 'KAY?

1159
00:57:25,075 --> 00:57:27,776
- 'KAY.
-  <i>'KAY, BYE.</i>

1160
00:57:27,778 --> 00:57:29,912
WHAT HAPPENED?

1161
00:57:29,914 --> 00:57:32,448
UH, UM...

1162
00:57:32,450 --> 00:57:35,451
APPARENTLY,
MY DAD'S GETTING MARRIED.

1163
00:57:35,453 --> 00:57:39,455
CONGRATULATIONS.

1164
00:57:39,457 --> 00:57:44,126
I GUESS.

1165
00:57:44,128 --> 00:57:45,994
WHERE'RE YOU GOING?

1166
00:57:45,996 --> 00:57:47,930
AH...

1167
00:57:47,932 --> 00:57:51,600
I'M GONNA GO
HAVE DINNER WITH DAD.

1168
00:57:51,602 --> 00:57:54,002
- WHY?
- UM...

1169
00:57:54,004 --> 00:57:57,840
APPARENTLY,
HE'S GETTING MARRIED.

1170
00:57:57,842 --> 00:58:00,242
GOOD FOR HIM.

1171
00:58:00,244 --> 00:58:05,013
HE WANTS ME
TO GO MEET HIS FIANCE SO...

1172
00:58:05,015 --> 00:58:07,115
HAVE FUN.

1173
00:58:07,117 --> 00:58:09,618
BE HOME AT A DECENT HOUR AND,

1174
00:58:09,620 --> 00:58:12,688
AND ALL THAT
PARENTING SHIT.

1175
00:58:12,690 --> 00:58:14,590
BYE, MOM.

1176
00:58:14,592 --> 00:58:19,127
LOVE YOU.

1177
00:58:19,129 --> 00:58:22,030
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

1178
00:58:22,032 --> 00:58:24,867
YOUR DAD TELLS ME
YOU'RE QUITE POPULAR AT SCHOOL.

1179
00:58:24,869 --> 00:58:26,568
[LAUGHS]

1180
00:58:26,570 --> 00:58:28,237
NO.

1181
00:58:28,239 --> 00:58:31,573
I'M ACTIVE,
BUT I'M, I'M NOT POPULAR.

1182
00:58:31,575 --> 00:58:33,842
WELL, HE'S PART OF
THE NEWSPAPER CLUB.

1183
00:58:33,844 --> 00:58:36,645
ACTUALLY,
I'M PRESIDENT OF
THE WRITERS' CLUB.

1184
00:58:36,647 --> 00:58:38,747
EDITOR OF
THE SCHOOL NEWSPAPER,

1185
00:58:38,749 --> 00:58:41,149
AND I RECENTLY JUST STARTED
A LITERARY MAGAZINE.

1186
00:58:41,151 --> 00:58:43,986
CHECK YOU OUT.
YOU MUST GET REALLY GOOD GRADES.

1187
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:45,988
YEAH,
HE DOES PRETTY WELL.

1188
00:58:45,990 --> 00:58:49,157
I HAVE A 4.3.
I WOULD HAVE A 4.5,

1189
00:58:49,159 --> 00:58:52,895
BUT I TEND
TO ARGUE WITH THE TEACHERS
AND THEIR LESSON PLANS SO.

1190
00:58:52,897 --> 00:58:54,530
WELL,
DO YOU PLAY SPORTS?

1191
00:58:54,532 --> 00:58:57,699
[LAUGHS]

1192
00:58:57,701 --> 00:58:59,535
I'M JUST...

1193
00:58:59,537 --> 00:59:02,838
I MEAN...

1194
00:59:02,840 --> 00:59:05,007
GOD KNOWS I TRIED.
WE'D ALWAYS GO DOWN

1195
00:59:05,009 --> 00:59:06,942
- TO THE PARK...
- DID WE?

1196
00:59:06,944 --> 00:59:09,077
THROW THE BALL AROUND,
BUT HE DIDN'T SHOW ANY INTEREST.

1197
00:59:09,079 --> 00:59:12,014
SO I QUICKLY REALIZED THAT
I DIDN'T GET THAT MAJOR LEAGUER

1198
00:59:12,016 --> 00:59:14,750
I WAS HOPING FOR.
HE KIND OF THREW LIKE A GIRL.

1199
00:59:14,752 --> 00:59:17,152
- DAD, WE, WE NEVER DID THAT.
- WELL, SURE WE DID.

1200
00:59:17,154 --> 00:59:20,055
YOU JUST DON'T REMEMBER.
I DON'T THINK YOU REMEMBER.

1201
00:59:20,057 --> 00:59:22,291
NO, I WOULD REMEMBER
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

1202
00:59:22,293 --> 00:59:25,027
HE'S ACTUALLY EXAGGERATING.
HE'S GOT A VERY SORT OF

1203
00:59:25,029 --> 00:59:27,095
CREATIVE IMAGINATION.
I THINK THAT'S WHAT MAKES HIM

1204
00:59:27,097 --> 00:59:29,998
- SUCH A GOOD WRITER.
- WHO ARE YOU PRETENDING TO BE?

1205
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,967
LIKE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU LEFT WHAT,

1206
00:59:31,969 --> 00:59:35,203
LIKE FIVE YEARS AGO WHEN I'VE
SEEN YOU TWICE SINCE THEN?

1207
00:59:35,205 --> 00:59:37,272
YOU'RE YOUNG,
MAYBE YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1208
00:59:37,274 --> 00:59:39,575
YOU'RE RIGHT,
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND

1209
00:59:39,577 --> 00:59:42,210
HOW YOU COULD JUST
ABANDON YOUR OLD FAMILY
AND THEN ACT LIKE

1210
00:59:42,212 --> 00:59:44,713
EVERYTHING IS OKAY
IN FRONT OF THE NEW ONE.

1211
00:59:44,715 --> 00:59:46,949
- CARSON, YOUR MOM'S UNSTABLE.
- YEAH, I KNOW.

1212
00:59:46,951 --> 00:59:49,685
- AND YOU LEFT ME WITH HER.
- CARSON...

1213
00:59:49,687 --> 00:59:51,253
YEAH, YOU KNOW, I CAN'T...

1214
00:59:51,255 --> 00:59:53,055
THANK YOU, APRIL.
THANK YOU FOR DINNER.

1215
00:59:53,057 --> 00:59:57,292
IT WAS LOVELY MEETING YOU,
BUT I HAVE TO GO.

1216
00:59:57,294 --> 01:00:01,063
CARSON, I CAN ONLY SAY SORRY
A NUMBER OF TIMES, BUT...

1217
01:00:01,065 --> 01:00:09,738
[SLAMS DOOR]

1218
01:00:09,740 --> 01:00:14,343
WELL,
HE'S HIS MOTHER'S SON.

1219
01:00:14,345 --> 01:00:24,386
<i>[TV PLAYING IN BACKGROUND]</i>

1220
01:00:24,388 --> 01:00:31,093
<i>[TV PLAYING IN BACKGROUND]</i>

1221
01:00:31,095 --> 01:00:33,695
<i>[PRINCIPAL] I'VE CALLED YOU</i>
<i>IN HERE TODAY TO ANNOUNCE</i>

1222
01:00:33,697 --> 01:00:35,998
<i>A NEW DISTRICT RULE MYSELF</i>

1223
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:38,634
<i>AND THE REST OF</i>
<i>THE PRINCIPAL BOARD FEEL</i>
<i>VERY STRONGLY ABOUT.</i>

1224
01:00:38,636 --> 01:00:40,402
SO STARTING NEXT SEMESTER,

1225
01:00:40,404 --> 01:00:44,106
ALL BOOK COVERS,
BACKPACKS AND CLOTHING

1226
01:00:44,108 --> 01:00:47,843
DISPLAYING LOGOS AND WRITING
ARE STRICTLY FORBIDDEN.

1227
01:00:47,845 --> 01:00:51,279
SO AS COUNCIL MEMBERS,
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT

1228
01:00:51,281 --> 01:00:54,416
THAT YOU HONOR THIS RULE
AND PROVIDE LEADERSHIP

1229
01:00:54,418 --> 01:00:56,652
- BY FOLLOWING IT.
- OKAY, AGREED,

1230
01:00:56,654 --> 01:01:00,922
I HATE SOME OF THE OBNOXIOUS
AND DEGRADING THINGS

1231
01:01:00,924 --> 01:01:03,692
THAT I READ EVERYDAY,
AND IF I SEE ONE MORE PERSON

1232
01:01:03,694 --> 01:01:05,661
WEARING ONE OF THOSE SHIRTS
THAT SAYS, "I DO MY OWN STUNTS,"

1233
01:01:05,663 --> 01:01:07,963
I'M GONNA PHYSICALLY RIP OFF
MY FACE AND THROW IT AT THEM.

1234
01:01:07,965 --> 01:01:10,899
BUT I MEAN, HOW ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO LEARN AND GROW

1235
01:01:10,901 --> 01:01:13,802
WHEN YOU KEEP TAKING
AWAY OUR BASIC FREEDOMS
OF SELF EXPRESSION?

1236
01:01:13,804 --> 01:01:15,804
TELL YOU WHAT, BUDDY,

1237
01:01:15,806 --> 01:01:18,206
WHY DON'T YOU JUST LET US
WORRY ABOUT STUDENT SUPPRESSION?

1238
01:01:18,208 --> 01:01:20,142
- HOW'S THAT?
- YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

1239
01:01:20,144 --> 01:01:22,244
YOU PEOPLE MUST KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING SINCE

1240
01:01:22,246 --> 01:01:24,346
MORE STUDENTS
ARE MORE DEPRESSED,
MORE STRESSED

1241
01:01:24,348 --> 01:01:26,415
AND DROPPING OUT NOW
MORE THAN EVER BEFORE

1242
01:01:26,417 --> 01:01:28,216
SO YOU'RE DOING
A REAL GREAT JOB
WITH THE DECISIONS.

1243
01:01:28,218 --> 01:01:30,185
- YOU'RE OUT OF LINE.
- YOU'RE ON A POWER TRIP.

1244
01:01:30,187 --> 01:01:33,055
HOW DOES BANNING LOGOS
DO ANYTHING EXCEPT HELP YOUR OWN

1245
01:01:33,057 --> 01:01:35,991
- CONSERVATIVE AGENDAS?
- THIS DISCUSSION IS OVER, OKAY?

1246
01:01:35,993 --> 01:01:39,027
YOU WILL
FOLLOW THE NEW RULES.
AND BECAUSE OF

1247
01:01:39,029 --> 01:01:41,697
YOUR DISRESPECTFUL ATTITUDE,

1248
01:01:41,699 --> 01:01:44,199
I HEREBY REVOKE ALL STUDENT
OFF-CAMPUS PRIVILEGES

1249
01:01:44,201 --> 01:01:46,835
FOR THE REST OF THE YEAR.

1250
01:01:46,837 --> 01:01:49,938
YOUR PEERS CAN THANK YOU,
LITTLE MAN.

1251
01:01:49,940 --> 01:01:55,911
LET'S GO, GUYS.

1252
01:01:55,913 --> 01:01:59,247
AAH! YOU CAN'T PUNISH
THE WHOLE SCHOOL

1253
01:01:59,249 --> 01:02:00,916
FOR ONE STUDENT'S
BIG MOUTH!

1254
01:02:00,918 --> 01:02:03,118
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU ALL JUST SAT THERE!

1255
01:02:03,120 --> 01:02:05,087
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE STILL
PUTTING THE BLAME ON US.

1256
01:02:05,089 --> 01:02:07,823
THANKS TO YOU,
WE HAVE TO HAVE PROM
IN THE CAFETERIA.

1257
01:02:07,825 --> 01:02:10,759
WE'LL BE SPENDING A LOT
OF TIME THERE SINCE WE CAN'T
GO OFF CAMPUS TO EAT ANYMORE.

1258
01:02:10,761 --> 01:02:13,295
IF YOU WRITE AN APOLOGY LETTER,
MAYBE THEY'D RECONSIDER.

1259
01:02:13,297 --> 01:02:15,731
HE SHOULD APOLOGIZE
TO THE WHOLE SCHOOL.

1260
01:02:15,733 --> 01:02:18,467
HM-HMM, WHAT ABOUT
NEXT WEEK AT ASSEMBLY?

1261
01:02:18,469 --> 01:02:20,969
OH, CARSON, YOU ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU WERE SO MUCH BETTER THAN US

1262
01:02:20,971 --> 01:02:23,105
BECAUSE WE ALL
COULDN'T STAND YOU,

1263
01:02:23,107 --> 01:02:25,774
BUT GET READY FOR
PURE HATRED COMING YOUR WAY
BECAUSE AS SOON AS

1264
01:02:25,776 --> 01:02:27,776
THE REST OF THE SCHOOL
FINDS OUT ABOUT THIS

1265
01:02:27,778 --> 01:02:30,445
AND THEY TELL THEIR PARENTS,
THE ENTIRE TOWN WILL ACTUALLY

1266
01:02:30,447 --> 01:02:32,380
- HATE YOU!
- ENOUGH, ALL RIGHT?!

1267
01:02:32,382 --> 01:02:35,016
I DIDN'T JUST
STAND UP FOR MYSELF IN THERE,

1268
01:02:35,018 --> 01:02:37,119
I WAS STANDING UP
FOR ALL OF YOU!

1269
01:02:37,121 --> 01:02:39,087
THE MINUTE YOU GUYS
WALKED INTO THIS CAMPUS,

1270
01:02:39,089 --> 01:02:41,089
YOU WERE LABELED
AS HIGH SCHOOL ROYALTY,

1271
01:02:41,091 --> 01:02:44,092
AND YOU'D RATHER
MAINTAIN THAT LABEL
THAN HEAVEN FORBID

1272
01:02:44,094 --> 01:02:46,161
STAND UP FOR YOURSELVES!

1273
01:02:46,163 --> 01:02:48,764
BUT HIGH SCHOOL ENDS,
AND FOR YOUR SAKES,

1274
01:02:48,766 --> 01:02:50,766
I HOPE GUYS AREN'T
THE WALKING CLICHES

1275
01:02:50,768 --> 01:02:52,768
EVERYONE THINKS YOU ARE!
'CAUSE LIFE IS GONNA

1276
01:02:52,770 --> 01:02:55,337
WALK ALL OVER YOU
AND IT'S GONNA
BITE YOU IN THE ASS!

1277
01:02:55,339 --> 01:03:06,081
WE ARE NOT CLICHES.

1278
01:03:06,083 --> 01:03:08,416
I TRIED AVOIDING YOU
AS LONG AS I COULD,

1279
01:03:08,418 --> 01:03:10,786
BUT THIS IS
THE ONLY PHARMACY IN TOWN,

1280
01:03:10,788 --> 01:03:23,899
AND I'M STARTING
TO GO THROUGH WITHDRAWAL.
SO I NEED MY REFILLS.

1281
01:03:23,901 --> 01:03:29,938
I FIGURED AS MUCH.

1282
01:03:29,940 --> 01:03:33,141
WOW. I KNOW WHAT
YOU MUST THINK OF ME.

1283
01:03:33,143 --> 01:03:36,945
PATHETIC DIVORCEE
WHO TURNED HERSELF INTO THIS.

1284
01:03:36,947 --> 01:03:40,015
WELL, THIS ISN'T
THE LIFE YOU WANT.

1285
01:03:40,017 --> 01:03:41,950
I GAVE HIM MY LIFE...

1286
01:03:41,952 --> 01:03:44,119
ONLY TO BE TOSSED ASIDE

1287
01:03:44,121 --> 01:03:46,955
WHEN HE DECIDED
IT WASN'T ENOUGH.

1288
01:03:46,957 --> 01:03:49,524
THIS WAS
NEVER A PART OF MY

1289
01:03:49,526 --> 01:03:54,529
PICKET FENCE FANTASY.

1290
01:03:54,531 --> 01:03:56,832
YOU AND I
AREN'T SO DIFFERENT.

1291
01:03:56,834 --> 01:03:58,900
I HAD A KID
TO SAVE A MARRIAGE,

1292
01:03:58,902 --> 01:04:01,837
AND YOU'RE HAVING ONE
TO ENSURE ONE.

1293
01:04:01,839 --> 01:04:04,573
SO YOU SHOULDN'T BE
SO QUICK TO JUDGE.

1294
01:04:04,575 --> 01:04:06,508
ESPECIALLY YOU.

1295
01:04:06,510 --> 01:04:10,979
'CAUSE I WAS YOU...

1296
01:04:10,981 --> 01:04:25,060
AND NOW I'M THIS.

1297
01:04:25,062 --> 01:04:27,863
SOMETIMES I JUST DON'T GET IT.

1298
01:04:27,865 --> 01:04:30,031
LIFE.

1299
01:04:30,033 --> 01:04:33,869
I MEAN, WHY DO
SOME OF US HAVE TO WORK

1300
01:04:33,871 --> 01:04:36,338
SO HARD FOR THINGS
WE BELIEVE IN

1301
01:04:36,340 --> 01:04:38,607
AND OTHERS DON'T?

1302
01:04:38,609 --> 01:04:42,944
